ENTRY       EC 3.5.1.50                 Enzyme
NAME        pentanamidase;
            valeramidase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on carbon-nitrogen bonds, other than peptide bonds;
            In linear amides
SYSNAME     pentanamide amidohydrolase
REACTION    pentanamide + H2O = pentanoate + NH3 [RN:R02938]
ALL_REAC    R02938
SUBSTRATE   pentanamide [CPD:C01842];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     pentanoate [CPD:C00803];
            NH3 [CPD:C00014]
COMMENT     Also acts, more slowly, on other short-chain aliphatic amides. Different from EC 3.5.1.49 formamidase.
HISTORY     EC 3.5.1.50 created 1984
